{% block column_2_content %}
<p>
  Buttons allow users to take actions, and make choices, with a single tap. Don't use them instead of a link.

  ID7 comes with Bootstrap button baked in, see the Bootstrap docs for <a
    href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/components/buttons/">full details </a> including sizing buttons.</p>
</p>

<h4> Rules </h4>

<ul>
  <li>Always use uppercase if possible</li>
  <li>Keep text on one line</li>
  <li>Icon is optional and can be placed either side of label</li>
</ul>

<p>Please see <a href="https://material.io/components/buttons/"> Material design </a> comprehensive guide to using
  buttons</p>

<p><strong>Most prominant buttons should alway use the secondary colour of the SO palette</strong></p>

<h4>Basic button: </h4>

<a href="#" class="btn btn-lg btn-brand-secondary">APPLY</a>

<!-- snippet start -->
<pre id="button-2" class="line-numbers language-markup snippet">
<code>
 <script type="prism-html-markup">
<a href="#" class="btn btn-lg btn-brand-secondary">APPLY</a>
  </script>
</code>
</pre>
<button class="btn btn-default" data-clipboard-target="#button-2">Copy snippet <i class="fal fa-copy"></i></button>


<hr>

